<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-04-06T11:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-04-06T11:00:00-05:00" n="360" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d360">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 837.51/303</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Cuba</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Gonzales</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-04-06T12:00:00-04:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">April 6, 1918, noon.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>Your April 5, 6 p.m. From previous conversation with Foreign
                                Minister, and from his written statement contained in my March 19,
                                11 a.m.,<note n="1" xml:id="d360fn1">Not printed.</note> Cuban
                                Government understands authority given Cuban Minister in document
                                transmitted in my March 13, midnight,<note n="2" xml:id="d360fn2">Not printed; see enclosure to the Cuban Minister’s note of
                                    March 18, <hi rend="italic">ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_322">p.
                                        322</ref>.</note> to be complete and absolute. Please,
                                therefore, express exactly the additional form desired so I may ask
                                for it. Legation has not the act of Congress of April 24, 1917.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Gonzales</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>